                                                                                                                                    Hyundai rolls out bus dream

     OUR BUREAU
             H.S. Lheem at the Auto Expo on Thursday. (PTI)
                 
	New Delhi, Jan. 10: Hyundai Motor plans to launch commercial vehicles in the country within a year and is looking for a joint venture with a local company.
    
	The company has shortlisted two firms and is close to selecting one, H.S. Lheem, managing director of Hyundai Motor India, said today.
    
	The Korean company plans to launch mid-size buses in the 25-seater category and large buses first, he said. Trucks will follow later.
    
	Hyundai Motor will launch the LPG variant of the Santro, its bestselling hatchback, by the end of September.
    
	The company today unveiled the variant at the auto show. 
    
	Renault facility
    
	Renault today said it would invest Rs 4,000 crore to set up a manufacturing unit in India, despite Mahindra amp; Mahindra pulling out of a joint venture that also involved Japanese firm Nissan. The plant will make four lakh units once it is fully operational, Renault India MD Sylvain Bilaine told reporters today. 
                                                                
